(1) btoa Method
----------------
==> encodes a string in base-64.
==> This method uses the "A-Z", "a-z", "0-9", "+", "/" and "=" characters to encode the string.
==> Syntax: btoa(String)

EX
---

	const str = "Hellow World"
	const encode = btoa(str)
	console.log(encode) // SGVsbG93IFdvcmxk
	
	
(2) atob Method
----------------
==> decodes a base-64 encoded string
==> This method decodes a string of data which has been encoded by the btoa() method.


EX
---

	const str = "Hellow World"
	const encode = btoa(str) 
	console.log(encode) // SGVsbG93IFdvcmxk
	const decode = atob(encode)
	console.log(decode)  // Hellow World
